    "text": [
        "A school of thought opines that creative people, namely musicians and painters, are not regarded much due to the augment of technology and science. However, artists have the blessings to potray feelings and capture minute details, which science is unable to comprehend. Undeniably, creativity should be given more boost.",
        "To embark on, one of the foremost strengths possessed by artists is to exhibit emotions while science does not have such mechanism. This is the thing that binds people together. To illustrate, singers\u2019 melodious voice reaches one\u2019s heart due to the presence of emotions, and the populace feels a connectivity, which is an impossible task for scientists. Similarly, painters produce paintings depicting varied phases of life intricately, which photographs can not. For example, M.F. Hussain, a renowned painter was revered for bringing minute details come alive through his craft. Hence, myriad other instances enlighten the worth of artists, which are beyond science\u2019s boundary.",
        "Furthermore, the art should be propagated without any qualms. One of the predominant reasons to aid art is that it nurtures culture. In the modernized era, the cultural ties are alleviating. Lyricist have all the means to promote and safeguard the rich culture. Moreover, artefacts and relics take us back to the ancient age and reminisce people of cultural heritage. Traditional songs revive the age-old customs and highlights the worth of ancestral traditions. This was, society is safeguarded from being fragmented.",
        "To recapitulate, it is believed that artists are not bestowed immense importance owing to the progress of technology and science. Nonetheless, a plethora of activities exists that are out of league for science but not for the art, and that is why art culture needs to be motivated."
